## Adding a New Grammar

To add support for a new grammar, follow these steps:

### 1. Create an Adapter

```typescript
// src/adapters/MyGrammarAdapter.ts
import { IGrammarAdapter, GrammarIR, ValidationResult } from '../types';

export class MyGrammarAdapter implements IGrammarAdapter {
  validate(spec: unknown): ValidationResult {
    // Return { valid: false, message: '...' } for invalid specs
    return { valid: true };
  }

  async render(ir: GrammarIR, container: HTMLElement): Promise<void> {
    // Render into container using your grammar's library
  }
}
```

### 2. Register the Adapter

```typescript
// In GrammarAdapterRegistry initialisation
GrammarAdapterRegistry.register('my-grammar', new MyGrammarAdapter());
```

### 3. Add a Node Descriptor

```typescript
// In getNodeDescriptor()
case 'my-grammar':
  return {
    lifecycle: useGrammarLifecycle,
    // ... other descriptor fields
  };
```

That's all. No new lifecycle file, no changes to the rendering pipeline.

